    "short_description": "A historic garden laid out in 1848, famous for its annual flower show and fossilized tree trunk.",
    "long_description": "The Government Botanical Gardens is a botanical garden in Udhagamandalam (Ooty), Tamil Nadu. The Gardens, divided into several sections, cover an area of around 55 hectares and lie on the lower slopes of Doddabetta peak. The garden has a terraced layout. It ascends the slopes of the hill in the form of ascending terraces. The garden was established in 1848. Its architect was William Graham McIvor. The gardens treasure a fossil tree trunk estimated to be 20 million years old.",
